title: ISC badminton tournament: Sajith-Iman duo wins title
text:
ISC badminton tournament: Sajith-Iman duo wins title L-R: Haridas P, Hareeshma, Mohammed Iman and Sajith before the family doubles final October 08, 2015 
The father-and-son team of Sajith and Mohammed Iman clinched the family doubles title at the annual badminton tournament, organised by Indian Social Club (ISC) Muscat, on Tuesday. 
In the final, Sajith and Iman beat the father-and-daughter team of Haridas P and Hareeshma 30-24. 
Meanwhile, the top-seeded pair of Sanjay Venkat and Anirudh Hariharan will take on third-seeded Jeswin Mathew and Iman in the final of the junior doubles. In the semifinals, Sanjay and Anirudh beat the all-girls duo of Gayathri Krishna and Ashpruha Patnaik 21-13, 21-6, while Jeswin and Iman upset the second-seeded pair of Milind Naithani and Adithya Hariharan 21-12, 17-21, 21-8. 
Also, Leon D’Souza will meet Jay Deshpande in the boys' U18 singles final. 
Leon beat Anirudh 21-12, 21-7, while Jay defeated Sanjay 22-20, 21-17. 
Other results: men’s doubles (quarters): Ronnie Pereira-Dominic Kennedy beat Manoj Varghese-Mathew Thomas 21-17,15-21, 21-18; Cyril William-Sudheer beat Errol D’Souza-Shebaz Nasar 21-16, 21-16; Prabhu A R-Niyas Nirar beat Vinod Abraham-Vineesh Mathew 21-9, 21-13. Similar content
